text: Bering Air Flight 445 was a scheduled domestic flight in Alaska, United States, from Unalakeet Airport to Nome Airport. On February 6, 2025, the Cessna 208B Grand Caravan operating the flight crashed in the Bering Sea. Of the 10 people on board, there were no survivors. A search is being done by the United States Coast Guard and is currently ongoing. ==References== Category:February 2025 events Category:2025 disasters in the United States Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 2025 Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in the United States Category:2020s in Alaska
